<subSubSection id="CFE3650DB0398807FF42FA7B98547326" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="87463686B0398807FF42FA7B996A72A6" blockId="7.[174,1233,1487,1802]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Hosts: American bison (P = 18.2 %; I = 24 (13–35)); markhor (P = 18.2 %; I = 13.5 (1–26)); European mouflon (P = 40 %; I = 14 (5–21)); Barbary sheep (P = 60 %; I = 37.7 (2–99)); saiga antelope (P = 8.7 %; I = 9 (8–10)); Ankole–Watusi (P = 100 %; I = 28); African buffalo (P = 100 %; I = 2); sika deer (P = 50 %; I = 4); red deer (P = 50 %; I = 3.7 (1–6)); guanaco (P = 33.3 %); I = 10); nilgai (P = 28.6 %; I = 3).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87463686B0398807FF42F91B99AC7286" blockId="7.[174,1233,1487,1802]" box="[227,1011,1679,1706]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Site of infection: abomasum (in markhor), small intestine, caecum.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87463686B0398807FF0FF93B9BE572E6" blockId="7.[174,1233,1487,1802]" box="[174,442,1711,1738]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">
